{"questionId":"12398","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f'\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, 0 ≤ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;≤ 5 is shown in the following diagram. The curve intercepts the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-axis at (1, 0) and (4, 0) and has a local minimum at (3, −1).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3cbb4bffa894dd2e849244395cf6acc76f04a7ec.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The shaded area enclosed by the curve <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f'\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-axis and the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>-axis is 0.5.&nbsp;Given that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( 0 \\right) = 3\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>,</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The area enclosed by the curve <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f'\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-axis between <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 1\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 4\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n</math></span> is 2.5 .</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Sketch the curve <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;0 ≤ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> ≤ 5 indicating clearly the coordinates of the maximum&nbsp;and minimum points and any intercepts with the coordinate axes.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/1c3139e91842a12e470381243ce0071e133228cc.png\"> &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> A1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>A1</strong></em> for correct shape over approximately the correct domain<br><em><strong>A1</strong></em> for maximum and minimum (coordinates or horizontal lines from 3.5 and 1 are required),<br><em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>-intercept at 3</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12398","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ1.H_8d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Sketch the curve y = f ( x ) , 0 ≤ x ≤ 5 indicating clearly the coordinates of the maximum and minimum points and any intercepts with the coordinate axes.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d"